org.rdkit.knime.nodes.smilesheaders

Class RDKitSmilesHeadersNodeModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • NodeModel
      • org.rdkit.knime.nodes.AbstractRDKitNodeModel
        • org.rdkit.knime.nodes.smilesheaders.RDKitSmilesHeadersNodeModel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TableViewSupport, RDKitObjectCleaner

    public class RDKitSmilesHeadersNodeModel
extends AbstractRDKitNodeModel
implements TableViewSupport
    This class implements the node model of the RDKitSmilesHeaders node providing functionality to set and change SMILES to be shown in column headers.
    Author:
    Manuel Schwarze

      • createInputDataInfos

        protected InputDataInfo[] createInputDataInfos(int inPort,
                                               DataTableSpec inSpec)
                                        throws InvalidSettingsException
        This implementation generates input data info object for the input mol column and connects it with the information coming from the appropriate setting model. This method needs to be implemented by a concrete node to generate InputDataInfo objects for each input column for all input tables. To find the proper column, the concrete node implementation must pass in the appropriate setting model of the column name into the constructor of the InputDataInfo class.
        Specified by:
        createInputDataInfos in class AbstractRDKitNodeModel
        Parameters:
        inPort - The port number of the input table to create input data objects for.
        inSpec - The table specification of the input table. Can be null.
        Returns:
        An array of info objects for all columns used as input for the passed table. Should not return null. If no input columns are used from the passed table, it should return an empty array.
        Throws:
        InvalidSettingsException - Thrown, if the current settings or the spec of the input table will make it impossible to process the data.

      • processing

        protected BufferedDataTable[] processing(BufferedDataTable[] inData,
                                         InputDataInfo[][] arrInputDataInfo,
                                         ExecutionContext exec)
                                  throws java.lang.Exception
        Description copied from class: AbstractRDKitNodeModel
        This method gets called from the method AbstractRDKitNodeModel.execute(BufferedDataTable[], ExecutionContext) to perform the main work of the node. It is equivalent to the original KNIME execute method. However, in this implementation the execute method acts more like a director to coordinate pre-, core and post-processing and to cleanup RDKit objects at the end. Hence, it should not be overridden. Instead a developer would override this method.
        Specified by:
        processing in class AbstractRDKitNodeModel
        Parameters:
        inData - The input tables of the node.
        arrInputDataInfo - Information about all columns of the input tables.
        exec - The execution context, which was derived as sub-execution context. Track the progress from 0..1.
        Returns:
        The result tables to be passed to the method AbstractRDKitNodeModel.postProcessing(BufferedDataTable[], InputDataInfo[][], BufferedDataTable[], ExecutionContext). If this method is not overridden these are the same tables that will be returned by the method AbstractRDKitNodeModel.execute(BufferedDataTable[], ExecutionContext) as the final result tables.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Thrown, if post-processing fails.

      • getOutputTableSpec

        protected DataTableSpec getOutputTableSpec(int outPort,
                                           DataTableSpec[] inSpecs)
                                    throws InvalidSettingsException
        Returns the output table specification of the specified out port. The implementation depends highly on the output generation strategy. If a ColumnRearranger is used to re-use the input table an output table specification will be based on that ColumnRearranger object. If a new table is created for an output port, it could generate a table specification directly derived from the an output factory. Returns the spec of the first input table as first output table and a new specification for the second output table.
        Specified by:
        getOutputTableSpec in class AbstractRDKitNodeModel
        Parameters:
        outPort - Index of output port in focus. Zero-based.
        inSpecs - All input table specifications. Can be null.
        Returns:
        The specification of all output tables.
        Throws:
        InvalidSettingsException - Thrown, if the settings are inconsistent with given DataTableSpec elements.

      • createWarningContextOccurrencesMap

        protected java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Long> createWarningContextOccurrencesMap(BufferedDataTable[] inData,
                                                                                            InputDataInfo[][] arrInputDataInfo,
                                                                                            BufferedDataTable[] resultData)
        Creates a map with information about occurrences of certain contexts, which are registered in the warning consolidator. Such a context could for instance be the "row context", if the warning consolidator was configured with it and consolidates warnings that happen based on certain malformed data in input rows. In this case we would list the row number of the input table (inData[0]) for this row context. The passed in parameters are for convenience only, as most of the time the numbers depend on them to some degree. The default implementation delivers a map, which contains only one context - the ROW_CONTEXT of the consolidator - and as total number of occurrences the number of input rows in table 0. Override this method for differing behavior. This implementation works with the row context on table 2 instead of table 1.
        Overrides:
        createWarningContextOccurrencesMap in class AbstractRDKitNodeModel
        Parameters:
        inData - All input tables of the node with their data.
        arrInputDataInfo - Information about all columns in the input tables.
        resultData - All result tables of the node that will be returned by the execute() method.
        Returns:
        Map with number of occurrences of different contexts, e.g. encountered rows during processing.
        See Also:
        AbstractRDKitNodeModel.getWarningConsolidator()
